OL,3,CInside Southern Water's 'super sewer'
OL,4,Ckeeping the sea off Brighton clean
OL,6,FSimon Judd at Southern Water said the
OL,7,Fsewers can "play a part" however. He
OL,8,Fsaid: "These projects are massively
OL,9,Fexpensive and they are not good for
OL,10,Fthe environment.
OL,12,F"So 150,000 metres cubed of water,
OL,13,Fthat's 150,000 tonnes that have to be
OL,14,Fpumped through our systems to the
OL,15,Fsewage treatment works, a colossal
OL,16,Famount of energy both to build
OL,17,Fprojects like this, the carbon cost of
OL,18,Fthe concrete and things to build them
OL,19,Fand then the carbon cost to pump that
OL,20,Faround.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
